title: For Sale:  WALTHER ~ PP EXTREMELY RARE WWII PISTOL w/ SA HOLSTER
postcontent: Here's a very scarce gun for the collector of WWII firearms! This is a Walther Model PP that was manufactured for the Sturmabteilung or "SA"...the Storm Troopers or "Brown Shirts" that functioned as a paramilitary protective organization for the Nazi Party. The SA played a key role in facilitating Adolf Hitler's rise to power in the 1920's and 1930's. This pistol was manufactured in about 1940 as evidenced by the Eagle/N proofs and serial number. The front grip strap is marked "SA der NSDAP Gruppe Hessen" which indicates it was issued to as SA leader within the state of Hesse in central Germany. Excellent original condition with 97-98% original bright blue finish. Contact me on my Email or my cell number 567-231-5075. Thank You.
